&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for a seasoned product leader to define and execute the product strategy for data and AI/ML products at Playlist. Playlist sits on the largest wellness data set in the world — a genuine competitive advantage — and this role exists to answer a deceptively simple question: which products should we build to unlock the value of that data, and what infrastructure do we need to leverage it at scale? You&#39;ll own both our flagship reporting and analytics products and a new generation of AI-powered products, building first for Mindbody before scaling across the broader Playlist portfolio.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a senior individual-contributor role with a clear path to grow into management. You&#39;ll partner with a strong, senior engineering team and stakeholders across the company, and you&#39;ll spend meaningful time with customers to validate what we build.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;About the role&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define the product strategy for company-wide data products — determining which reporting/analytics and AI-powered products to build to maximize the value of Playlist&#39;s wellness data, and the infrastructure required to deliver them at scale.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and grow our flagship analytics products while building net-new products from zero to one — concepting, validating, and shipping into white space.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the development of AI-powered products such as agent-driven reporting and the creation of new data assets, including modeling and aggregating data for machine learning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously improve the user experience of data and AI/ML products, balancing the realities of a probabilistic AI environment with the rigor of a deterministic data environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Validate proofs of concept directly with customers, spending regular time on customer calls to ground decisions in real needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead ideation, evaluation, definition, and prioritization of the squad roadmap, scoping the highest-ROI opportunities for a cross-functional team of engineers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build alignment with stakeholders across the organization, seeking a range of perspectives and soliciting honest feedback in a heavy enterprise stakeholder environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Synthesize quantitative and qualitative data to inform key product decisions, and drive measurable impact alongside a senior engineering team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Skills &amp;amp; experience&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have a track record shipping impactful, well-loved data, analytics, or AI/ML products, with experience spanning both data science and product management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have proven zero-to-one experience — concepting and shipping new products into white space — alongside the ability to scale and optimize mature products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are deeply analytical and product-intuitive, fluent in defining, querying, and interpreting your own data, and you anchor

